<subsection name="Update Archive Status" id="ArchiveStatus">
<p>
When documents are loaded into the Registry, their archive status is set to "STAGED".
You can update archive status of one or more documents by lidvid or package id (Harvest run id). 
</p>
<source>
Usage: registry-manager set-archive-status &lt;options&gt;

Set product archive status

Required parameters:
  -status &lt;status&gt;    One of the following values:
      ARCHIVED
      ARCHIVED_ACCUMULATING
      IN_LIEN_RESOLUTION
      IN_LIEN_RESOLUTION_ACCUMULATING
      IN_PEER_REVIEW
      IN_PEER_REVIEW_ACCUMULATING
      IN_QUEUE
      IN_QUEUE_ACCUMULATING
      LOCALLY_ARCHIVED
      LOCALLY_ARCHIVED_ACCUMULATING
      PRE_PEER_REVIEW
      PRE_PEER_REVIEW_ACCUMULATING
      SAFED
      STAGED
      SUPERSEDED
  -lidvid &lt;id&gt;        Update archive status of a document with given lidvid, or
  -packageId &lt;id&gt;     Update archive status of all documents with given package id
Optional parameters:
  -solrUrl &lt;url&gt;      Solr URL. Default is http://localhost:8983/solr
  -zkHost &lt;host&gt;      ZooKeeper connection string, &lt;host:port&gt;[,&lt;host:port&gt;][/path]
                      For example, zk1:2181,zk2:2181,zk3:2181/solr
  -collection &lt;name&gt;  Solr collection name. Default value is 'registry'
</source>

<p>
Below are few examples.
</p>
<source>
registry-manager set-archive-status IN_QUEUE -lidvid urn:nasa:pds:context:target:asteroid.4_vesta::1.1
registry-manager set-archive-status ARCHIVED -packageId 8d8ae96d-044e-473d-a278-62635b1c5977
</source>

</subsection>


